<br>
...ahh, a subject that's been gnawing at me for a while now...<br>
<br>
Vision, as most of you know, is a fairly large guild.  We've seen our share of players come and go over the last couple years.  Sometimes people retire.  Sometimes people move on to other guilds.<br>
<br>
Looking at the guild history of the vast population of the server, it's pretty fair to say that membership in at least at few guilds over the course of your character's life is normal.  People don't join Vision having never been in a guild.  And although it does happen, people don't normally leave Vision to remain guildless.  At least early in your &quot;life&quot; guild membership might be a little like joining the Y.  You go a few times, you make sure there aren't too many creeps at in the gym, and you see if the Tae Kwon Do class fits your work schedule.<br>
<br>
While some of us might have the big &quot;4-Life&quot; tattoo on the webbing between our thumb and index finger, not everyone's guild allegiance is so permenant.  I regularly have people who want to hunt the biggest targets in the game leave Vision to want to join EW/CB/VV/SoT.  Some of them return, some of them become fine members of the &quot;bigger&quot; guilds.  Conversely, people leave EW/CB/VV/SoT on a regular basis as well - landing in nearly every guild on the server for reasons too numerous to sum up in my little rant...<br>
<br>
&lt;rant&gt;<br>
<br>
But what ticks me off are the people who disguise their motives.  I will not forgive those who joined my guild - who pretended to be part of my family - only so they could get the experience, the equipment, and the reputation necessary to move on to a &quot;better&quot; guild.  I will not forgive those who &quot;couldn't play during PST hours&quot; who, upon joining an EST guild, continue to play long into the nights even after I go to sleep.  I will not forgive those who &quot;just wanted a change of scenery&quot; when the change of scenery is always to a guild who kills bigger targets.  I will not forgive those who felt &quot;they didn't belong&quot; who felt very much like they belonged when they begged daily for help with their epic, their armor, their weapons or their spells.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> I will not forgive those who did not have the courage to look their guildmates in the eye and say the truth.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
&lt;/rant&gt;<br>
<br>
Ranting aside.  I wish the best of luck to every ex-Vision member who has taken another path in this game.  I hope every one of them is happy.  I honestly do. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4868>Palimax Sceleris</a>, Guildleader <a href=http://www.guildvision.org>Vision</a>, Grandmaster <a href=http://www.base-nine.org/available_tinkering_items.htm>Tinkerer</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uvaxumgax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>vaxumgax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/14/02 10:53:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1481.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: All about Sejah</span><hr size=1> Palimax, you forgot the exception of Judamus... To hell with him...<br>
